			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Aggro<a name="57199"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 7:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As to whether we have an aggro modifier that impacts everything, I don't think so, it doesnt fit with my experience.  Many of our songs are reduced aggro however.
<br />

<br />
I don't believe this is necessarily the case with chants.  You just need to understand how they work and then modify your tactics to it.  
<br />

<br />
You get the aggro for the damage you do... as a dot... from a distance usually.  That its from a distance means you will get less aggro than someone in melee range (same is true for casters and priests).  That its a dot means that its not major aggro right away.  If you want to kite for the group, you need a little lead.  If all your chants have hit for 2 pulses now the group needs to catch up to you and you can keep the aggro just fine.  
<br />

<br />
Also, I have found that snared mobs behave differently than unsnared mobs (even if its not your snare).  Unsnared mobs are much more likely to aggro on sitting casters, snared mobs will not divert to seated folks just for the sake of sitting.
<br />

<br />
So let me take the spot wehere I do kiting groups most often these days... HoH graveyard.  I am the kiter in general, occassionally a necro may just outstrip me damagewise and take it away.  When I pull, I snare the mob on inc, and let my chants build up a head  of steam before it gets to the group.  If I've done 5% damage or so before anyone else lands a spell, and 3 or 4 chants are going full steam, along with resnaring until that gets covered... that sucker is mad at ME and I am the drum major in a really BIZARRE parade...
<br />

<br />
Hehe, I was grouped with a couple necros and a couple mages there, various pets in tow.. I  got inspired to make a hotkey:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
/em sings There were 76 spectres in the big parade...
<br />
/em sings With 110 skeletons close at hand...
<br />
/em sings They were followed by rows and rows of the finest elementals...
<br />
/em sings Derived, from Air, Sea, Fire and Land...
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />
But I had no trouble keeping the aggro.</span></td>
