			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Aggro<a name="58281"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 22 04 7:21 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>From my experience, Rey's assessment is spot on.
<br />

<br />
While we're on the subject, what do you think of the proposed OOW AA Discordant Melodies.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5833&amp;source=Test">Discordant Melodies Level 1</a> - Increases hate by 20% on all of our detrimental songs for 1 min
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5834&amp;source=Test">Discordant Melodies Level 2</a> - Increases hate by 50% on all of our detrimental songs for 1 min
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5835&amp;source=Test">Discordant Melodies Level 3</a> - Increases hate by 100% on all of our detrimental songs for 1 min
<br />

<br />
I personally hate it for a few reasons:
<br />

<br />
1.  They stealth nerfed the aggro on our chants only to give it back to us in the form of AA.  I think this practice is reprehensible in general.
<br />

<br />
2.  It doesn't address the reasons bards want aggro in the first place.  The 2 main reasons cited in all of the debates are:
<br />

<br />
(a.) So bards can tank lower-end single group content like easy LDoNs.  With a 1 min duration and presumably a long recast time (I know it says 'Recast: 0' but so does Boastful Bellow so the recast must be coded another way.) bards can't use it for the duration of an xp group.
<br />
(b.) For snap aggro in crisis situations.  I can't tell you how many times in KT the tank has gone down and the mob makes a beeline for the cleric.  If I could get snap aggro for a very short period of time (long enough to finish off a KT mob in a regular xp group) it would save the group from a wipe.  I wouldn't care if our snap aggro ability had a long recast time or cost 2000 mana since I would only want to use it when things were really bad.  
<br />

<br />
As a solution, I think they should handle adding aggro for bards in two ways:
<br />

<br />
A.  Change the AA to a snap aggro ability.  Yes, give us taunt but make it limited by mana or a reuse timer.  (I would prefer it being limited by mana so that it could scale with gear upgrades and give me a reason to care about upgrading past the 'I have enough HP to live through raids and enough mana to pull constantly' level.  Even with the higher end GoD zones, HP and mana upgrades don't actually increase bard power very much past a certain point, but this is another discussion for tCH.)
<br />

<br />
B.  Give us an aggro song.  I would like it to be coded to give a certain amount of hate per cast and allow it to be pulsed.  That way if a bard wanted to tank they could give up the other songs in their twist to gain aggro.  It would be a tradeoff.
<br />

<br />
My 12cp (adjusted for inflation),
<br />
Calli</span></td>
