				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Aggro<a name="58809"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 12:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>/agree with Calliopeia about the new AA.  
<br />

<br />
If it is on a timer, it will suck, unless it is PURELY an oh-crap, over-the-top snap aggro.  From the description, however, it is not.  It is presented as an incresing percentage, not a &quot;lump sum&quot; of hate.
<br />

<br />
Mana based, (though I HATE the entire notion of Bard using Mana for ANYTHING), at least gives flexibility of timing, while still putting a strong limiter on its use.  (Like Fading Memories).  I TOTALLY don't care about the gear thing though.  Anything that makes us more gear dependent, I am generally NOT for.  This is one of the main reasons I have loved my Bard.  My gear sucks, and I'm still one of the best Bards on my server, tyvm.
<br />

<br />
A pulsed Taunt Song, &quot;Nya-nya-nya-nya-nyaaaaa-nyaaaa&quot;, this is an excellent idea.  You give up other songs for this ability to hold aggro for kites and/or easy-tanking situations.
<br />

<br />
Of course, giving us A CHARM WE CAN ACTUALLY USE IN XP GROUPS would solve the &quot;oh crap get em off the cleric&quot; problem easily enough.  Back when I could actully USE my Charms in groups, I saved many a caster by charming the mob off them.
<br />

<br />
As for holding aggro on an HoH kite, I would twist thus:
<br />

<br />
Snare, Chant_01, Chant_02, Snare, Chant_03, Chant_04, repeat...
<br />

<br />
It has always been the case, however, that people would have to WAIT for the Bard to build aggro before engaging.  This is not a new concept to the game, but it seems these days people don't get it.  Depending on the dps output of the group, they adjust what percent HP they engage at.  If they get aggro, then the wait longer next time.  It's really no big deal, but it DOES require cooperation and a little patience.
<br />

<br />
As for the general question of &quot;should a Bard be able to tank?&quot;  I'm not sure.  I think that without lots of AAs and nice gear, our base damage mitigation is a joke.  When a well geared, pajama-wearing Caster can out-tank me, something is fundamentally WRONG with the game.  I'm wearing Plate Mail, last time I checked.  If I were the DM, hehe, this would NEVER happen...
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
