				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Aggro<a name="58816"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 1:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Obviously there are situations where a bard CAN tank effectively IF the bard can hold agro.  This AA obviously doesn't do anything to make that a more realistic possibility and Calli is totally on-target with her analysis.  It is a typical situation of Sony recognizing a basic need but implementing a solution that tries to address two separate and disparate variations which cannot be fixed with the same solution.  Sustained agro for tanking cannot be accomplished with a 1 minute ability.  Burst agro for emergencies cannot be applied in gradually increased levels of agro.  Consequently, we have two situations where we need to hold agro and by trying to fulfill both, Sony effectively manages to create an AA that can do neither one.
<br />

<br />
In my normal XP group, it is not at all uncommon for me to be chain pulling stuff in Plane of Fire.  When our tank decides to take a break, I keep pulling.  I bring a mob and start tanking.  Within 10 seconds, the shaman will have agro and now HE'S tanking for the rest of the fight while I just do my best to apply melee damage.  Not that we can't kill several mobs that way without problems, but you know, like Klapton says, it's pretty silly to be running around in plate armor with a pair of swords and have an ogre in purple fishnet tights take agro away from me at will and then do just as good a job holding off the mob as I could.</span></td>
