				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;If I mezz a mob then an enchanter mezzes the same mob, it breaks and goes to the enchanter&quot;
<br />

<br />
If I mezz a mob, it breaks and goes to whoever is standing next to it, or whoever just had a spell land. Proximity aggro is greater than mezz aggro unless I've been holding it for awhile. I love that feature personally. 
<br />

<br />
We used to do kite groups while LFG or waiting on a tank to arrive. Since we're the only ones that can cast and run at the same time, it makes sense for us to be the ones that hold aggro. While it varied from zone to zone, still I could hold aggro well enough to keep it off pursuing pets. And what the h*ll was wrong with that? If it were all dots that had reduced aggro, we could still keep aggro off a druid. Having the others wait until the mob is at 60% isn't really an answer. I don't mind 90. Whoever the partners are, they will do more damage so the sooner then can start in the better.
<br />

<br />
I think a hate song would have been great. Let us choose when we want the aggro, but still require we build it up over time. Or swap an instrument in to get faster hate. Snap aggro sounds too much like taunt and that is reserved for the true tanks, so I think it's a bit too much to ask for.</span></td>
